caption:
Visited Turin with mom and sis 🤍
She wanted to see Venaria Reale and so I brought her, and while she marveled at the white vaults for the first time I reminisced how I had the entire location closed off for a day for one of my shootings.
Then we went to the Egyptian museum, and as she marveled at the ancient statues I reminisced how I was the first fashion photographer to ever shoot in the most important temples of Luxor and the tomb of Nefertari, the most exquisitely conserved tomb in ancient history, a place that accepts visits of merely 15 minutes a day. The things I’ve done, the places I’ve seen.
I will never take it for granted. I really lived a life worth of a movie and I owe it to you Mamma, the first to ever believe in me, when you first saw me from across the livingroom at 15 and said ‘ you really catch fire when you have the camera in your hands ‘ 
📸
I love you.
